The Senate, on Tuesday, read the letter of President Muhammadu Buhari signifying his resumption of office after spending about 50 days in the United Kingdom on vacation. The letter was read by Senate President Bukola Saraki on the floor of the upper house of legislation during plenary. The President cited Section 145 of the Nigerian constitution to inform the Senate of his resumption of office from March 13, 2017. He sent a similar letter to Yakubu Dogara, the Speaker of the House of Representatives.  Click Here>>>>>>Anti-kidnap and anti-theft device for tracking and listening<<<<<< 